716603f-a.folder: Baxter Street & Grand Street, Manhattan, NY
716603f-a.text:
151-155 Baxter Street, east side, south of Grand Street. No. 153 is a three-story frame building with a brick front.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 310.

718545f-a.folder: Centre Market Place & Grand Street, Manhattan, NY
718545f-a.original_title: Manhattan: Centre Market Place - Grand Street
718545f-a.text:
Centre Market Place, north from Grand, to and including Broome Streets. Building shown on the left, is the Central Headquarters of the New York Police
Depattment.
June 9, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
